  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity Development for sector-wide policy and plans in the Gulf States</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SDGs represent a paradigm shift in the way countries address challenges and opportunities in education. We draw lessons from policy research and practice to facilitate peer learning among states to bolster reform efforts and facilitate national level tracking of progress towards SDG4 targets. Five of the seven SDG 4 targets focus on measurable and cross-nationally comparable learning outcomes (4.1, 4.2, 4.4, 4.6 and 4.7). Within SDG 4 framework, we provide technical advice and capacity development opportunities to MoEs in Gulf States with a view to strengthening capacities in educational policy, mapping data and data sources to monitor learning, as well as in strengthening educational financial data at national level as part of consensus to implement the Arab SDG 4 Road Map in the Gulf.</narrative>
  </description>
